<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="109" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,424,2071]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,251,424,450]" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Diagnosis</emphasis>
:—Plants of 
<taxonomicName box="[389,633,424,450]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benbothae">
<emphasis box="[389,633,424,450]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Kalanchoe benbothae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[646,730,424,450]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[196,1393,198,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[166,1422,187,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Kalanchoe benbothae from Vaalbank, KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa. A. Inflorescence section lateral view. B. Pseudo-rosette base of a flowering plant. C. Flower of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right) lateral view. D. Flower of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right) dorso-lateral view. E. Pistil with squamae of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right). F. Ben Botha (1961–) for whom the species is named. Scale bars:A: 4 mm; B: 25 mm; C–D: 8 mm; E: 4 mm. Photographs by the authors (A–E) and B.A. Botha (F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5533585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5533585/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) are medium-sized to large, glabrous, densely waxy when young, bi- to triennial to perennial succulents that can be separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1908" box="[892,995,460,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[892,995,460,486]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">K. luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1013,1083,460,486]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1991,2013]" captionTargetBox="[196,1422,190,1936]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[166,1422,190,1966]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Kalanchoe luciae. A. Inflorescence section lateral view, close up showing dense waxy covering. B. Inflorescence section lateral view. C. Pseudo-rosette showing intensely red-infused leaves. D. Flowering plant colony, Botha’s Hill. Scale bars: A: 15 mm; B: 25 mm; C: 75 mm; D: 12 cm. Photographs by the authors." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5533589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5533589/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), its closest relative, as follows: 
<taxonomicName box="[136,382,496,522]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benbothae">
<emphasis box="[136,382,496,522]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Kalanchoe benbothae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less robust in all vegetative respects than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1908" box="[887,989,496,522]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[887,989,496,522]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">K. luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with especially the leaves of the former (90–140 × 
<quantity box="[259,396,532,559]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" unit="mm" value="80.0" valueMax="100.0" valueMin="60.0">60–100 mm</quantity>
) not attaining the dimensions of the latter (40–160(–190) × 20–90(–110) mm) (
<figureCitation box="[1298,1386,532,558]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[196,1393,198,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[166,1422,187,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Kalanchoe benbothae from Vaalbank, KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa. A. Inflorescence section lateral view. B. Pseudo-rosette base of a flowering plant. C. Flower of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right) lateral view. D. Flower of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right) dorso-lateral view. E. Pistil with squamae of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right). F. Ben Botha (1961–) for whom the species is named. Scale bars:A: 4 mm; B: 25 mm; C–D: 8 mm; E: 4 mm. Photographs by the authors (A–E) and B.A. Botha (F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5533585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5533585/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). The flowers of 
<taxonomicName box="[257,407,568,594]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benbothae">
<emphasis box="[257,407,568,594]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">K. benbothae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are lightly to moderately covered in a waxy bloom (
<figureCitation box="[995,1084,568,594]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[196,1393,198,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[166,1422,187,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Kalanchoe benbothae from Vaalbank, KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa. A. Inflorescence section lateral view. B. Pseudo-rosette base of a flowering plant. C. Flower of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right) lateral view. D. Flower of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right) dorso-lateral view. E. Pistil with squamae of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right). F. Ben Botha (1961–) for whom the species is named. Scale bars:A: 4 mm; B: 25 mm; C–D: 8 mm; E: 4 mm. Photographs by the authors (A–E) and B.A. Botha (F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5533585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5533585/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
), while those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1908" box="[1271,1372,568,594]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[1271,1372,568,594]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">K. luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a substantial waxy bloom (
<figureCitation box="[415,539,604,630]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1991,2013]" captionTargetBox="[196,1422,190,1936]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[166,1422,190,1966]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Kalanchoe luciae. A. Inflorescence section lateral view, close up showing dense waxy covering. B. Inflorescence section lateral view. C. Pseudo-rosette showing intensely red-infused leaves. D. Flowering plant colony, Botha’s Hill. Scale bars: A: 15 mm; B: 25 mm; C: 75 mm; D: 12 cm. Photographs by the authors." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5533589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5533589/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Fig. 2A–B</figureCitation>
). The corolla lobes of 
<taxonomicName box="[785,935,604,630]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benbothae">
<emphasis box="[785,935,604,630]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">K. benbothae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reddish pink and triangular, while those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1908" box="[136,236,640,666]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[136,236,640,666]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">K. luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are white to pale yellowish green and oblong (
<figureCitation box="[755,912,640,666]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[196,1393,198,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[166,1422,187,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Kalanchoe benbothae from Vaalbank, KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa. A. Inflorescence section lateral view. B. Pseudo-rosette base of a flowering plant. C. Flower of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right) lateral view. D. Flower of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right) dorso-lateral view. E. Pistil with squamae of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right). F. Ben Botha (1961–) for whom the species is named. Scale bars:A: 4 mm; B: 25 mm; C–D: 8 mm; E: 4 mm. Photographs by the authors (A–E) and B.A. Botha (F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5533585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5533585/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Fig. 1A, C–D</figureCitation>
). The anthers of 
<taxonomicName box="[1096,1245,640,666]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benbothae">
<emphasis box="[1096,1245,640,666]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">K. benbothae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reddish brown in bud, while those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1908" box="[391,492,676,702]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[391,492,676,702]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">K. luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are yellow, and the pistil of the former is narrowly elliptic, whereas that of the latter species is prolate. 
<taxonomicName box="[345,591,712,738]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benbothae">
<emphasis box="[345,591,712,738]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Kalanchoe benbothae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has transversely oblong nectar scales, while those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1908" box="[1202,1304,712,738]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[1202,1304,712,738]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">K. luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are ± square (
<figureCitation box="[144,230,748,774]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1952,1974]" captionTargetBox="[196,1393,198,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[166,1422,187,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Kalanchoe benbothae from Vaalbank, KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa. A. Inflorescence section lateral view. B. Pseudo-rosette base of a flowering plant. C. Flower of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right) lateral view. D. Flower of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right) dorso-lateral view. E. Pistil with squamae of K. benbothae (left) and K. luciae (right). F. Ben Botha (1961–) for whom the species is named. Scale bars:A: 4 mm; B: 25 mm; C–D: 8 mm; E: 4 mm. Photographs by the authors (A–E) and B.A. Botha (F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5533585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5533585/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
